<paragraph id="050DF464FFEDFFEFD7E0341897CBCB1E" blockId="3.[94,719,858,1043]" lastBlockId="3.[794,1417,218,275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
This genus is extremely rare in collections and known only from a few specimens. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEDFFEFD560343894B2C9BE" author="Machado, R. J. P. &amp; Rafael, J. A." pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="22 - 28" refId="ref11474" refString="Machado, R. J. P. &amp; Rafael, J. A. 2011. A new species of Fillus Navas, 1919 (Neuroptera: Ascalaphidae) from the Brazilian Amazon Basin. Zootaxa, 2907: 22 - 28." type="journal article" year="2011">Machado &amp; Rafael (2011)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="C2B28FE7FFEDFFEFD64834D895F9C9BE" authorityName="Machado &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2011" box="[300,495,922,947]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Fillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonicus">
<emphasis id="37C62876FFEDFFEFD64834D895F9C9BE" box="[300,495,922,947]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fillus amazonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Brazilian Amazon basin from 
<specimenCount id="13B43FEDFFEDFFEFD65B34F895A4C9DE" box="[319,434,954,979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="13B43FEDFFEDFFEFD68E34F89663C9DE" box="[490,629,954,979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
, providing detailed illustrations of abdominal characters of both sexes. 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEDFFEFD7C034B89556CE1E" author="Penny, N. D." box="[164,320,1018,1043]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="391 - 406" refId="ref12267" refString="Penny, N. D. 1981 a. Review of the generic level classification of the NewWorld Ascalaphidae (Neuroptera). Acta Amazonica, 11 (2): 391 - 406. http: // www. scielo. br / pdf / aa / v 11 n 2 / 1809 - 4392 - aa- 11 - 2 - 0391. pdf." type="journal article" year="1981">Penny (1981a)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="61238995FFEDFFEFD61134B89693CE1E" author="Machado, R. J. P. &amp; Rafael, J. A." box="[373,645,1018,1043]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="22 - 28" refId="ref11474" refString="Machado, R. J. P. &amp; Rafael, J. A. 2011. A new species of Fillus Navas, 1919 (Neuroptera: Ascalaphidae) from the Brazilian Amazon Basin. Zootaxa, 2907: 22 - 28." type="journal article" year="2011">Machado &amp; Rafael (2011)</bibRefCitation>
point- ed out that 
<taxonomicName id="C2B28FE7FFEDFFEFD4C63798901BCAFE" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1919" box="[930,1037,218,243]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Fillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brethesi">
<emphasis id="37C62876FFEDFFEFD4C63798901BCAFE" box="[930,1037,218,243]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">F. brethesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C2B28FE7FFEDFFEFD32C379890C6CAFE" baseAuthorityName="Van der Weele" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[1096,1232,218,243]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Acmonotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paradoxus">
<emphasis id="37C62876FFEDFFEFD32C379890C6CAFE" box="[1096,1232,218,243]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">F. paradoxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could represent the same species.
</paragraph>
